AB  - This paper provides a summary of the five papers published in this special issue. It also indicates the themes that connect these papers and highlights the major insights uncovered by the research. The overall message is that banks adapt in often-unexpected ways to the dynamic nature of regulation and the complex interaction of regulation and the evolving market forces that spawn frontier risks and amplify traditional risks, thereby creating daunting regulatory challenges.
